dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. "The results of Dr. Kane's expedition, by favour of the royal Geographical Society." In upper margin: III. Includes 11 illustrations and bird's eye views surrounding the maps: H.M.S. Terror thrown up by the ice in Frosen Strait, "Prince Albert" surrounded by icebergs in Melville Bay (W. Parker Snow), Cape Hotham with H.M.S. Pioneer and Resolute, Esquimaux female, Seal hunting, Building snow hut (Kennedy's 2nd voyage of the "Prince Albert), Sledge travelling (Osborne's arctic journal), Walrus or horse, and Esquimaux man and boy. Plate 3 from: The royal illustrated atlas of modern geography. London ; Edinburgh : A. Fullarton and Co., [1862?]
